Velvet students in concert with Charles University choirs
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical game.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from higher and secondary schools.
The highlight of the festival consists of two concerts on November 17.
"Charity University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs are the Chorus of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the festival committee sits Rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes which takes place with free entry on 17 November from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening there is the concert "Vilvet Students" in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools and that of Charles University perform.
