The basis of this long-term strategy was cast by the first head of the firm, the visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left the slogan that a large number of global problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
His slogan 'PENSE' has become the imprint around which the life of a giant future will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began to edit in 1935).
It was the basis of Watson's careful enterprise culture.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years because it always remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
It allowed us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more" depleted for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
