Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A typist of Cali has moved on to the story as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano'.
The work of these officials is crucial.
In November 4 a typist of Cilicopac has passed to the story as the person who confirmed the identity of the False Chief: "Alfonso Cano", by comparing his fingerprints.
Of the seven typists working in the local offices of the CTI, this week was the "availability" tour of Eliazar Gonzalez, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the field of judicial investigation for 21 years.
Early in his career, Gonzalez worked in the Munich Caps, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to get to the place where the corpses were to be identified.
In the year 2000 he was transferred to the capital of Valle and after attending suitable courses, he specialized in typing, which is the study of the friction skin, i.e. the palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter in Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected that one of them was the one of the man who ran the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to carry the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo Leon Soenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the site, he didn't recognize it by its physical appearance, because it was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed as a peasant in the area, without glasses and much leaner.
But the fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a sampler and a lantern, Eliazar compared the corpse's fingerprints with those on the map.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the official who confirmed to the Minister of Defence, Juan Carlos Pinzon, that yes, he was the supreme leader of the FARC.
In search of the footprint
For a typist from Sijon de Cali, President Juan Manuel Santos's recognition of Eliazar Gonzalez in a press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don't know our job.
Plasyloscopy is an exact, no-great-great-great-great-great-great-great-great-great-great-great-g
Apart from identifying the bodies, the typists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many offenders present false identity cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and look for them in the database.
The researcher told that in one flight he had to remove a part of a wall from a house, because in that place the thief had pressed his hand to take out a safe full of jewelry and money.
'The walls are difficult because they are not adequate areas to make a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to get the imprint with all the hand and identify the offender who had been involved in different flights,' he recalls.
The fingerprints may also dismiss or confirm suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently we found a dead man, with bottles of drink around him.
The investigation was determined that a parent may be suspected of the crime and indeed a mark on the bottle coincided.
Even if it does not guarantee that he is the murderer, it places him on the crime scene.
A CTI fingerprinting explained that "final fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents" are extracted.
When they appear, a sampler or a strip is used to take them.
Subsequently, the fingerprints are sent to Asif, the Declining Database, or to the National Civil Registry.
'The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians,' the CTI expert said.
He explained that not everything is how the CSI television programme is shown.
As not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched necessarily becomes a imprint.
It can, however, be used if the necessary confrontation is realized.
